<section id="sub" class="section">
    <div class="py-4 px-2 px-sm-4">
        <div class="section-heading mb-4">
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-between section-toggle"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#subCollapse" role="button" 
                aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="subCollapse">
                <h2 class="display-6 w-100 d-flex m-0">
                    Substitution cipher
                </h2>
                <span class="text-light px-1 border bg-dark border-dark rounded align-self-end">
                    <i class="bi bi-arrow-up lh-base"></i>
                </span>
            </div>
            <hr>
            <p class="text-dark px-2">
                Where a Caeser cipher simply shifts the position of the alphabet to the left or right a number of times, a substitution cipher uses a key or a phrease to make a new alphabet - the end result potentially being a completely jumbled up alphabet. 
            </p>
            <p class="text-dark px-2">
                A quick example substitution: 
                <code class="d-inline-flex px-2 text-dark bg-success bg-opacity-10 border border-success border-opacity-10 rounded-2">
                    SENTANCE
                </code> → 
                <code class="d-inline-flex px-2 text-dark bg-success bg-opacity-10 border border-success border-opacity-10 rounded-2">
                    TEST
                </code>
                → 
                <code class="d-inline-flex px-2 text-dark bg-success bg-opacity-10 border border-success border-opacity-10 rounded-2">
                    QBLRBLSB
                </code> 
                - The full alphabet would look like 
                <code class="d-inline-flex px-2 text-dark bg-success bg-opacity-10 border border-success border-opacity-10 rounded-2">
                    TESABCDFGHIJKLMNOPQRUVWXYZ
                </code> &ndash; notice that T, E and S have moved to the start, the second T in TEST isn't present again as it has already been used and placed. There is more information available on the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Substitution_cipher" class="text-convrtr">Substitution cipher</a> Wikipedia page. 
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="collapse" id="subCollapse">
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card">
                    <span class="card-label visually-hidden">Substitution cipher</span>
                    <div class="card-body text-center">
                        <textarea placeholder="Example: TEST SENTENCE → WORD [key] → PSJW OSEWABTH" title="Vigenere string" rows="6" id="subText" class="form-control sub-cipher"></textarea>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-footer text-dark py-3">
                        <div class="text-center mb-4 g-0">
                            <div class="row row-cols-2 g-md-0 gx-0 gy-2">
                                <div class="col col-12 col-md-auto">
                                    <div class="input-group w-auto">
                                        <label class="input-group-text" id="substitution-group" for="subKey">Key</label>
                                        <input type="text" class="form-control" id="subKey" title="Substitution cipher key">
                                        <button class="btn btn-outline-convrtr" type="button" id="subEncrypt">Encrypt</button>
                                        {% comment %}<button class="btn btn-outline-convrtr" type="button" id="subDecrypt" title="Decryption is currently unavailable">Decrypt</button>{% endcomment %}
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col d-flex flex-fill justify-content-end">
                                    {% include "components/select-copy-dl" %}
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <hr />
                        <div id="subResults" class="data-to-copy active"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>